<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hie" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hie,</orth> (used only in the pres. and impf.) 1) intr. to make haste: <cit><quote>away she --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1189" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1189</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>who to her mistress --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1215" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1215</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>charging the groom to h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1215" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1215</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>doth h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1215" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1215</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>and thither --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 153.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 153, 12</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 4, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.355" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 355</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.5.82" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 5, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.347" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 347</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 4, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.5.39" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.286" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 286</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.4.25" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.290" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 290</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 1, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl><lb />2) refl. (the simple personal pronoun always serving as reflexive): <cit><quote>Adonis --d him to the chase,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 3" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>unto the wood they h. them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 3" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 3</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 2, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.4.12" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 4, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.73" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 73</bibl>. Oftenest in the imperative: <bibl n="shak. pp 167" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.178" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 178</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.181" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 181</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.4.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 4, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.325" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 325</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.143" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 70</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 70</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.164" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.3.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 3, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 5, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 3, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.194" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 194</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.3.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 3, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 3.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. III, 1, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.241" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 241</bibl>.
